value.name: Maggie
value.overview: Maggie is an American comedy television series starring Ann Cusack. The series premiered August 18, 1998, on Lifetime Television.

value.name: Maggie
value.overview: As a psychic, Maggie regularly sees the future of her friends, parents, clients and random strangers on the street, but when she suddenly sees a glimpse of her own future, she is forced to start living in her own present.

value.name: Maggie
value.overview:
Maggie is a British television series produced by the BBC between 1981 and 1982. It was based on a quartet of books written by Joan Lingard during the 1970s - 'The Clearance', 'The Resettling', 'The Pilgrimage' and 'The Reunion'.

Set in the city of Glasgow, the series centred around teenager Maggie McKinley and the problems of adolescence as she aspired to further education, a career and an independent life whilst her parents expected her to take a secure job, get married and "settle down". Much of the action also centred around Maggie staying with her feisty octogenarian grandmother in Inverness-shire: the latter frequently acted as an important confidante to her granddaughter. The two series followed Maggie's progress, ending as she faces a crossroads in her life - whether to go to university or work for the family business. The theme music was by pop star B. A. Robertson.

value.name: Maggie
value.overview: A supernatural, quirky comedy about Maggie and her recently deceased friend, Adam. Only Maggie and can see and hear Adam, which can create some pretty awkward situations for Maggie, and Maggie's a girl who needs no help with awkward.

value.name: Maggie & Bianca Fashion Friends
value.overview: Originally polar opposites, an American fashion student and the daughter of an industry mogul form an everlasting bond and start a rock band in Milan, Italy.

value.name: Maggie
value.overview: Based on books by Erma Bombeck, Maggie Weston is a housewife living with husband Len and sons Mark and Bruce outside of Dayton, Ohio. There is a third son, LJ, who is never seen because he's "always in the bathroom." Rounding out the main cast are Maggie's friends.

value.name: Maggie Briggs
value.overview: Maggie Briggs is an American sitcom television series that aired from March 4 until April 15, 1984. The original title for the show was Suzanne Pleshette Is Maggie Briggs.

value.name: Maggie and the Ferocious Beast
value.overview: A precocious 5-year-old named Maggie conjures up an imaginary land where she and her favorite toys, Hamilton Hocks and Ferocious Beast, can play and have adventures. The Ferocious Beast is anything but ferocious, though he is large, with red spots and three horns on his head.

value.name: Maggie Winters
value.overview: Maggie Winters is a short-lived CBS sitcom that ran from 1998 to early 1999. The title character was played by Faith Ford.

value.name: The Trouble with Maggie Cole
value.overview: What happens when idle gossip escalates out of control and starts to affect people’s lives. Set in a picturesque fishing village, the series centres on Maggie Cole, the self- appointed oracle of this close-knit community.

value.name: Maggie Beer's Big Mission
value.overview: Australia's food icon, Maggie Beer, leads an ambitious world first social experiment to transform the meals and dining experience at an aged care home.

value.name: Maggie and the Ferocious Beast: Puzzles and Picnics
value.original_name: Maggie and the Ferocious Beast: Puzzles and Picnics
value.overview: Set in the imaginary world of Nowhere Land a brave and smart girl named Maggie and her two friends the rather cuddly misnamed Beast and the very particular pig Hamilton Hocks show preschoolers that friendship makes everything more fun! Foster your child's curiosity and problem-solving skills with these episodes: Picnic Time, Recipe For Trouble, The Lemonade Stand, The Big Carrot, A Visit to Cake Town, and The Big Hat.

value.name: Tea and Biscuits with Maggie Pritchard
value.original_name: Tea and Biscuits with Maggie Pritchard

value.name: Brian and Maggie
value.overview: A dramatization of the story behind and occasion of Thatcher’s last TV interview, the hugely damaging ITV grilling by her old friend Brian Walden, which some view as the final nail in her prime ministerial coffin.

value.name: The Buzz on Maggie
value.overview: Maggie Pesky is an unusual young teen fly with big dreams. Maggie gets the community's attention with her antics in a conventional world of upstanding flies. Maggie is always plotting to make even mundane tasks fun and exciting.
